{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T17:36:26.557Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Jacobian and Hessian matrices"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are higher-order derivatives that generalize the gradient and derivative concepts to handle functions with multiple inputs and outputs. The Jacobian captures "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "first-order sensitivity"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (how each output changes with each input), while the Hessian captures "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "second-order curvature"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (how the rate of change itself changes), enabling advanced optimization and deeper understanding of model behavior."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Jacobian & Hessian ‚ÄĒ concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is ‚ÄĒ Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient (1st-order, scalar output):"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a function "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "f(x‚āĀ, x‚āā,..., x‚āô)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that outputs a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "single number"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "‚ąáf = [‚ąāf/‚ąāx‚āĀ, ‚ąāf/‚ąāx‚āā, ..., ‚ąāf/‚ąāx‚āô]  (vector, n√ó1)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient = vector of partial derivatives"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Jacobian (1st-order, vector output):"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a function "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "g(x‚āĀ, x‚āā,..., x‚āô)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that outputs "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "multiple numbers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (g‚āĀ, g‚āā,..., g‚āė):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "J_g = [‚ąāg‚āĀ/‚ąāx‚āĀ  ‚ąāg‚āĀ/‚ąāx‚āā  ...  ‚ąāg‚āĀ/‚ąāx‚āô]\n      [‚ąāg‚āā/‚ąāx‚āĀ  ‚ąāg‚āā/‚ąāx‚āā  ...  ‚ąāg‚āā/‚ąāx‚āô]\n      [  ...      ...    ...    ...   ]\n      [‚ąāg‚āė/‚ąāx‚āĀ  ‚ąāg‚āė/‚ąāx‚āā  ...  ‚ąāg‚āė/‚ąāx‚āô]  (matrix, m√ón)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Jacobian = matrix of ALL partial derivatives"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hessian (2nd-order, scalar output):"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a function "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "f(x‚āĀ, x‚āā,..., x‚āô)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that outputs a single number:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "H_f = [‚ąā¬≤f/‚ąāx‚āĀ¬≤   ‚ąā¬≤f/‚ąāx‚āĀ‚ąāx‚āā  ...  ‚ąā¬≤f/‚ąāx‚āĀ‚ąāx‚āô]\n      [‚ąā¬≤f/‚ąāx‚āā‚ąāx‚āĀ ‚ąā¬≤f/‚ąāx‚āā¬≤    ...  ‚ąā¬≤f/‚ąāx‚āā‚ąāx‚āô]\n      [  ...        ...       ...    ...      ]\n      [‚ąā¬≤f/‚ąāx‚āô‚ąāx‚āĀ ‚ąā¬≤f/‚ąāx‚āô‚ąāx‚āā  ...  ‚ąā¬≤f/‚ąāx‚āô¬≤  ]  (matrix, n√ón)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hessian = matrix of ALL second-order partial derivatives"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Quick comparison:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Concept"}]}]}, {"typ